comments.text:
Alright. Regarding the constant claim of Sundar Pichai being in Google because of his IIT education...that's a tiny bit misleading. 

Not many people know that Sundar's engg stream in IIT wasn't computers, but Metallurgy. That's as far anyone can be from Computers as is humanly & technically possible within engineering. He worked in some other company as a materials engineering after his IIT.

He later did his MS in US in the same branch i.e. Materials science. After his little stint as material engineer, he did his MBA from Stanford, after which he took the standard route that most South Asian students take, which is joining a Big4 consulting firm. In Sundar's case, it was McKinsey. It was after McKinsey that Sundar got into Google.

In one of the profiles done many years ago, another Indian-American Google head Vic Gundotra said Larry Page chose Sundar to head Google as he has observed him as a product leader & manager for the Chrome browser, and he was a no-frills, not-much-politics team player.

So yeah, Sundar Pichai being the Google CEO is more to do with his Stanford MBA than his IIT education. I'm sure his IIT network must have helped him in US, though.
